article.headline: DaQuan Smith hits 3-pointer at the buzzer and Radford takes down South Carolina Upstate 64-61
article.description: — DaQuan Smith hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer and Radford defeat South Carolina Upstate 64-61 on Saturday.
article.linkText: DaQuan Smith hits 3-pointer at the buzzer and Radford takes down South Carolina Upstate 64-61
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- — DaQuan Smith hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer and Radford defeat South Carolina Upstate 64-61 on Saturday. Bryan Antoine had 18 points and seven rebounds for the Highlanders (12-8, 2/3 Big South Conference). Kenyon Giles scored 15 points and added five assists. Smith had 10 points and shot 3 for 10, including 2 for 7 from beyond the arc. Trae Broadnax led the way for the Spartans (6-12, 1-4) with 20 points. South Carolina Upstate also got 14 points, 10 rebounds, two steals and two blocks from Nick Alves. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
